Was very impressed with this place. The portion sizes and value are great. The service was very friendly. My wife and I thoroughly enjoyed our food and date night.  We both loved the cheese curds. The salmon was cooked literally perfectly.

One critique would be the acoustics were kinda echoy in the place. Sounded a bit off. Not sure how to fix that but it could use a sound engineer to figure out the space.

Sage and Barrel is a vibe!
First off, shoutout to Jackie! She is an absolute gem. She made the whole experience feel like we were VIPs. She was funny, kind, and super attentive without hovering. We appreciated her so much!
Now onto the food and drinks‚Ä¶
Let me just say this: I‚Äôve had a lot of mules in my day. Theirs was easily Top 3. The Old Fashioned was also a solid drink. It was smooth and very flavorful.
As for the food:
‚Ä¢	The fish and chips were next level. Perfectly golden and flaky inside.
‚Ä¢	The other dish was Chops Diane. It was pure comfort food with elevated flavors. Also, those veggies weren‚Äôt just a side, they were actually seasoned and GOOD.
‚Ä¢	Even the empty appetizer basket got a moment of appreciation. Would recommend the cheese curds but they didn‚Äôt stand a chance to photos.
This place gets everything right. The flavor, service, and atmosphere were 10/10. Will definitely be back. If you‚Äôre thinking about going‚Ä¶ just do it. And ask for Jackie! üòÅ

Sage and Barrel is super yummy with large creative variety and a cool vibe.  We had excellent service üëèüèª  and it wasn't too busy. The only thing thay could improve ...the food took a long time to come out but I think it is good to take your time to make delicious food and have time to chat. The other draw back was the cost. Prices were higher than most in its class but our dates thought the price was well worth it!

We've been here two times now. The first time we were a little drunk so we tried it again...
Amazing.
The prices resemble a ma' and pa' shop, and yet the flavor resembles a fine dining experience.

Today we had Cynthia as our waitress and just like our first time, the waiting was great. Friendly, nice, and refills on the drink were always on time.

I've paid a lot more money at other restaurants for less service and taste than here.

Please give them your business.

This is such an adorable place! The ambience is so gorgeous. It‚Äôs a perfect place for a first date or an evening out with the girls. The drinks are top notch, the appetizers are huge and the food is delicious! I highly recommend the blueberry lemon mule for a cocktail and the brussel sprouts for the appetizer. The service was fantastic. It was a little pricey, but the portions were fair for the price. I highly recommend you give it a try!

Sage & Barrel is a nice place for a casual meal. I attended as President for our team social event. Essentially, it was a business meal for our volunteers to enjoy social time with each other.

There was 11 of us; it was not enuff people for the separate room. We could have used the separate room, as it was difficult to hear during conversations. It would have been helpful for us to be placed in the separate room.

It was really noisy in the venue til about 6pm. Then the people there just for drinks left, which quickly made the room quieter.

The food was good. All of us were pleased with our meal. Some of us had dessert; the desserts were good. Drinks were refilled quickly, which is nice on a hot day. Food and drink prices were as expected, given the nature of these things now.

The wait staff was quite efficient and pleasant. The waitress was quite patient with us; she explained what was in some meals [spices, some ingredients] for a few group members.

The table was cleared of plates and flatware in the expected length of time. The owner stopped by to say "thank you for coming here," which was a nice and unexpected touch.

We will go back to Sage & Barrel again for future social events.  Sept 2025

detailedReviews.author: Bill Ringling
detailedReviews.text:
First time here 9.5.25 745ish... Had no expectations but a good meal. Looked at menu and was impressed large selection and variety of options.  The decor and energy felt very good upon entering. Although quite loud, and 80% filled was a very good vibe. Met immediately,  sat quickly. Took several minutes to be greeted by server, slow but expected to a degree.

Ordered appetizer Brussel sprouts perfect delicious. I ordered crispy chicken breast with mashed and gravy with green beans. Beans delicious but way overcooked, mashed whipped smooth but near little flavor and same with gravy in my opinion which is expected in some places, unexpected here especially when advertised as herbed seasoned. The crispy chicken was absolutely juicy and easily cut with just a fork, tenderly prepared golden brown. The breading plain and bland otherwise diminishing a wonderful chicken breast. Overall, my meal was nothing I would choose to order again. The other meal was fish and chips which frankly was darn good comparatively despite its own hurdles.  A huge whole fillet, not greasy, hot and tender. Way too much breading but likely necessary to hold such a long fillet together. But not certain. The tartar sauce was surprisingly tasty and had a hint of bite perhaps horseradish...but delicious and cold. The fries completely fresh cut and fried golden brown but very soggy and I know the reason as to why.

Those who read my reviews know im brutally honest be it a 1 or a 10...sequencing food takes a level of precision and kitchen management knows this fact.  Our brussel sprouts came out late (probably 12.15 minutes from order) the runner delivered and said your food is up as she is delivering appetizer and asked if we wanted it now. Of course we said no as we wanted the sprouts or else why order as an appetizer right?. That spelled doom to me who grew up in my father's restaurant business. Although delicious,  appetizers can and did harm the meal from timing and sequencing. Fries when delivered were no longer crispy but soggy soft, gravy on mashed potatoes had filmed over instead of being wet and steamy. They had to bring out our meal before we got done with sprouts because of an error along the communication channels and somebody was finally paying attention to how much time they were sitting. Now, we have a filled table of dishes, food not delivered as intended by the chef, and a not so shiny review because the meal is the ultimate prize or is intended to be such. This is not on our server at all and 3 star service is because of the mistakes I outlined above and below.

I know it's hard to find or develop chemistry on and in any team with so many moving parts. I do think somebody needs to work on that from kitchen to table. If I were to have another experience like this a 2nd time, I would absolutely not go back a 3rd time. Mistakes happen. Same mistakes, that's a trend management is responsible for.

One final item unfortunately to share. An advertisement for a tiny signature drink for $12 should be if nothing else good or bad needs to be crafted consistent. I was driving,  so I did not order the "lemon drop" advertised drink but I did have a sip of each. First one was more yellow than the 2nd one which was more pink. 1st one had a fresh lemon slice and was very very tart.  The 2nd had a dried lime slice and was much sweeter both had a sugary rim. How can they be so different if the recipe is used or did bartender(s) just do whatever they chose? I don't know but the inconsistencies across food and drinks makes me question what's going on there.

Maybe it was a bad night for some? Maybe understaffed or new staff? Maybe something else? I know the kitchen definitely faltered.

I will go back as I firmly believe stuff happens and there may not be an explanation determination and a 2nd chance is nearly always deserved especially with a restaurant.  Time will make the determination.

detailedReviews.text: We have had the opportunity to dine at Sage & Barrel a number of times over the last year or so..  It really has become one of our favorite spots and the food is very good. Negative reviews and reputation issues (e.g., offering free desserts for 5-star reviews, inconsistent drink quality) - review management can address this concern
Lack of atmosphere/ambiance awareness (e.g., noise levels affecting conversation, cozy atmosphere not highlighted) - social media marketing can improve this area

positive.author: ES
positive.text:
Sage & Barrel is a nice place for a casual meal. I attended as President for our team social event. Essentially, it was a business meal for our volunteers to enjoy social time with each other.

There was 11 of us; it was not enuff people for the separate room. We could have used the separate room, as it was difficult to hear during conversations. It would have been helpful for us to be placed in the separate room.

It was really noisy in the venue til about 6pm. Then the people there just for drinks left, which quickly made the room quieter.

The food was good. All of us were pleased with our meal. Some of us had dessert; the desserts were good. Drinks were refilled quickly, which is nice on a hot day. Food and drink prices were as expected, given the nature of these things now.

The wait staff was quite efficient and pleasant. The waitress was quite patient with us; she explained what was in some meals [spices, some ingredients] for a few group members.

The table was cleared of plates and flatware in the expected length of time. The owner stopped by to say "thank you for coming here," which was a nice and unexpected touch.

We will go back to Sage & Barrel again for future social events.  Sept 2025

neutral.author: Bill Ringling
neutral.text:
First time here 9.5.25 745ish... Had no expectations but a good meal. Looked at menu and was impressed large selection and variety of options.  The decor and energy felt very good upon entering. Although quite loud, and 80% filled was a very good vibe. Met immediately,  sat quickly. Took several minutes to be greeted by server, slow but expected to a degree.

Ordered appetizer Brussel sprouts perfect delicious. I ordered crispy chicken breast with mashed and gravy with green beans. Beans delicious but way overcooked, mashed whipped smooth but near little flavor and same with gravy in my opinion which is expected in some places, unexpected here especially when advertised as herbed seasoned. The crispy chicken was absolutely juicy and easily cut with just a fork, tenderly prepared golden brown. The breading plain and bland otherwise diminishing a wonderful chicken breast. Overall, my meal was nothing I would choose to order again. The other meal was fish and chips which frankly was darn good comparatively despite its own hurdles.  A huge whole fillet, not greasy, hot and tender. Way too much breading but likely necessary to hold such a long fillet together. But not certain. The tartar sauce was surprisingly tasty and had a hint of bite perhaps horseradish...but delicious and cold. The fries completely fresh cut and fried golden brown but very soggy and I know the reason as to why.

Those who read my reviews know im brutally honest be it a 1 or a 10...sequencing food takes a level of precision and kitchen management knows this fact.  Our brussel sprouts came out late (probably 12.15 minutes from order) the runner delivered and said your food is up as she is delivering appetizer and asked if we wanted it now. Of course we said no as we wanted the sprouts or else why order as an appetizer right?. That spelled doom to me who grew up in my father's restaurant business. Although delicious,  appetizers can and did harm the meal from timing and sequencing. Fries when delivered were no longer crispy but soggy soft, gravy on mashed potatoes had filmed over instead of being wet and steamy. They had to bring out our meal before we got done with sprouts because of an error along the communication channels and somebody was finally paying attention to how much time they were sitting. Now, we have a filled table of dishes, food not delivered as intended by the chef, and a not so shiny review because the meal is the ultimate prize or is intended to be such. This is not on our server at all and 3 star service is because of the mistakes I outlined above and below.

I know it's hard to find or develop chemistry on and in any team with so many moving parts. I do think somebody needs to work on that from kitchen to table. If I were to have another experience like this a 2nd time, I would absolutely not go back a 3rd time. Mistakes happen. Same mistakes, that's a trend management is responsible for.

One final item unfortunately to share. An advertisement for a tiny signature drink for $12 should be if nothing else good or bad needs to be crafted consistent. I was driving,  so I did not order the "lemon drop" advertised drink but I did have a sip of each. First one was more yellow than the 2nd one which was more pink. 1st one had a fresh lemon slice and was very very tart.  The 2nd had a dried lime slice and was much sweeter both had a sugary rim. How can they be so different if the recipe is used or did bartender(s) just do whatever they chose? I don't know but the inconsistencies across food and drinks makes me question what's going on there.

Maybe it was a bad night for some? Maybe understaffed or new staff? Maybe something else? I know the kitchen definitely faltered.

I will go back as I firmly believe stuff happens and there may not be an explanation determination and a 2nd chance is nearly always deserved especially with a restaurant.  Time will make the determination.
